---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page
  title="Design System"
  description="Visual showcase of design tokens, typography, colors, and components"
>
  <header class="section">
    <h1>Design System</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-secondary">
      Visual showcase of design tokens, typography, colors, and components
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="stack-xl">
    <section class="section-sm">
      <h2>Golden Ratio Layout Grid</h2>
      <p>
        Our layout uses a three-column CSS Grid system with Named Lines,
        creating optimal reading experiences through Golden Ratio mathematics.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">Mathematical Foundation</h3>
      <p>
        The Golden Ratio (φ ≈ 1.618) creates harmonious proportions. In our
        layout: <strong>Content = φ² × Gutter</strong>
      </p>
      <div class="surface" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
        <code>--phi: 1.618</code><br />
        <code>--phi-squared: 2.618</code><br />
        <code>--measure: 65ch</code> (optimal reading length)<br />
        <code>--gutter: clamp(1rem, 5vw, calc(65ch / 2.618))</code> ≈ 24.8ch max
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">Default: Content Column</h3>
      <p>
        By default, all content stays within the optimal reading column (~65ch).
        This text is an example of the default layout.
      </p>

      <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">Breakout: Content + Gutters</h3>
      <p>Use <code>.breakout</code> to span content plus both gutters:</p>
      <div
        class="breakout surface"
        style="margin-top: var(--space-4); background-color: var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-bg); padding: var(--space-6); text-align: center;"
      >
        <strong>This element spans the breakout zone</strong>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-2);">
          Content column + left gutter + right gutter
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-2); opacity: 0.9;">
          <code>.breakout</code> class applied
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-6);">Full-Width: Edge-to-Edge</h3>
      <p>Use <code>.full-width</code> to span the entire viewport:</p>
    </section>

    <div
      class="full-width"
      style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-secondary-40) 0%, var(--color-secondary-60) 100%); color: var(--color-bg); padding: var(--space-12); text-align: center; margin-block: var(--space-6);"
    >
      <h3 style="color: var(--color-bg); margin-block-end: var(--space-2);">
        Full-Width Hero Section
      </h3>
      <p style="margin-block-end: 0; opacity: 0.95;">
        This spans edge-to-edge across the entire viewport
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-2); opacity: 0.9;">
        <code>.full-width</code> class applied
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="section-sm">
      <h3>Layout Usage Summary</h3>
      <div class="stack" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>Default (no class)</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Content column only (~65ch). Optimal for reading text.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>.breakout</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Content + both gutters. Good for images, diagrams, and figures.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>.full-width</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Edge-to-edge. Use for hero sections and full-bleed images.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-sm">
      <h2>Grid System (Spacing)</h2>
      <p>All dimensions conform to a <strong>0.5em grid unit</strong>.</p>
      <div class="surface" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
        <code>--grid-unit: 0.5em</code>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-sm">
      <h2>Typography</h2>
      <h3>Headings</h3>
      <h1>Heading 1</h1>
      <h2>Heading 2</h2>
      <h3>Heading 3</h3>
      <h4>Heading 4</h4>
      <h5>Heading 5</h5>
      <h6>Heading 6</h6>

      <h3>Body Text</h3>
      <p>This is regular body text.</p>
      <p class="text-lg">Large text</p>
      <p class="text-sm">Small text</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section-sm">
      <h2>Responsive Breakpoints</h2>
      <p>
        Our breakpoint tokens define key screen sizes for managing responsive
        behavior at a global level.
      </p>
      <div class="stack-lg" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>--breakpoint-small: 620px</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Small screens, typically mobile devices
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>--breakpoint-medium: 960px</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Medium screens, such as tablets
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface">
          <strong>--breakpoint-wide: 1365px</strong>
          <p
            style="margin-top: var(--space-1); color: var(--color-text-secondary);"
          >
            Wide screens, accommodating most desktop displays
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-sm text-center">
      <p><a href="/" class="font-medium">← Back to Home</a></p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Page>
